definition.value: A tricarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate groups of 5,6,7,8-tetrahydrosarcinapterin; major species at pH 7.3.
beta-Ergocryptine in which a single bond replaces the double bond between positions 9 and 10.
Compounds with a 1,2,4-triazoline skeleton.
The alpha-anomer of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-D-glucosamine.
The beta-anomer of N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-D-glucosamine.
Compounds with a 1,2,3-triazoline skeleton.
The N-formyl derivative of maleamic acid.
Compounds with a 1,2,4-triazolidine skeleton.
Compounds with a 1,2,3-triazolidine skeleton.
A compound containing pyrrole rings connected by methylene units.
A compound containing three pyrrole rings connected by methylene units.
A polyalkyl-substituted tripyrrane dicarboxylic acid, a precursor of a porphyrin system.
The monohydrate form of ciprofloxacin monohydrochloride.
A compound containing a small number of fluorene units.
The dihydrochloride salt of ciprofloxacin.
An oligofluorene containing three fluorene units.
A biflavonoid that consists of two units of 5,7,4'-trihydroxyflavanone joined together at position 3 and 3''.
An amphipholic trifluorene having hexyl and N,N-bis(2-hydroxyethyl)aminophenyl side-chains.
A surfactant molecule possessing both hydrophilic and lipophilic properties.
A hexasaccharide derivative that is a hexaarabinofuranoside corresponding to part of the arabinomannanan portion of the lipoarabinomannan from Mycobacterium tuberculosis.
A tetrasaccharide derivative that is a methyl tetraarabinofuranoside corresponding to part of the arabinomannanan portion of the lipoarabinomannan from Mycobacterium tuberculosis.
A tetrasaccharide derivative that is a methyl tetraarabinofuranoside corresponding to part of the arabinomannanan portion of the lipoarabinomannan from Mycobacterium tuberculosis.

A member of the class of morpholines that is cis-2,6-dimethylmorpholine in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a racemic 2-methyl-3-[p-(2-methylbutan-2-yl)phenyl]propyl group. An inhibitor of the action of squalene monooxygenase, Delta(14) reductase and D7-D8 isomerase and an antifungal agent, it is used (generally as its hydrochloride salt) for the topical treatment of fungal nail and skin infections.
The (2S)-enantiomer of 2-ureidoglycine.
A branched hexasaccharide corresponding to part of the lipooligosaccharide from N. gonorrhoeae L8.
The zwitterion resulting from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the alpha-amino group of (S)-2-ureidoglycine.
The angular furanocoumarin analogue of the linear furanocoumarin marmesin.
A branched undecasaccharide corresponding to part of the lipooligosaccharide of N. meningiditis type L7
The trialkylammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of neopinone.
An imidazopyridine having norleucine and ornithine residues attached via their side-chains at the 4- and 2-positions respectively.
The [4,5-b]-fused isomer of imidazopyridine.
The trialkylammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of thebaine.
A beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine in which the anomeric hydroxy group has beta configuration.
The dianion obtained by removal of two protons from the phosphate group of D-glycero-D-manno-heptose 7-phosphate.
An organic cation consisting of beta-carboline having methyl and hydroxy substituents at the 2- and 6-positions respectively.
The tetra-anion obtained by removal of all of the protons from the phosphate groups of D-glycero-D-manno-heptose 1,7-bisphosphate.
A (6E)-nerolidol in which the hydroxy group at positon 3 adopts an S-configuration.

A (6E)-nerolidol in which the hydroxy group at positon 3 adopts an R-configuration. It is a fertility-related volatile compound secreted by the queens of higher termites from the subfamily Syntermitinae.
A member of the cadinene family of sesquiterpenes in which the isopropyl group is cis to the hydrogen at the adjacent bridgehead carbon
An isomer of selinene where the double bond in the octahydronaphthalene ring system is endocyclic (2R,4aR,8aR)-configuration..

A member of the class of hydroxypyrimidines obtained by cyclocondensation of L-arginine and methylglyoxal; a methyl glyoxal-derived advanced glycation end-product (AGE) in familial amyloidotic polyneuropathy and human cancers.
An imidazolium ion formed via cyclo-dimerisation of L-lysine and methylglyoxal.
The cation resulting from protonation or quaternisation at the 3-position of any 1H-imidazole.
An imidazolium ion formed via cyclo-dimerisation of L-lysine and glyoxal.
The beta-anomer of ADP-D-glycero-D-manno-heptose.
Dianion of ADP-D-glycero-beta-D-manno-heptose arising from deprotonation of both free OH groups of the diphosphate.
A pyrrole formed via Maillard reaction of epsilon-aminocaproic acid with glucose.
